# OWASP Security

Apply on every feature. Skills: `owasp-security-check`, `laravel-security`, `laravel-security-audit`, project `security-audit`.

## A01 Access Control

- Public API (`/api/v1`): read-only GET only; no auth bypass on admin routes.
- Admin routes: `auth:sanctum` + `EnsureUserIsAdmin` — never skip middleware.
- Enforce ownership: filter by `school_id` / user scope in repository, not controller alone.
- Return **404** (not 403) when record exists but user lacks access — prevents IDOR enumeration.

```php
// ✅ GOOD — scoped query prevents IDOR
$this->newQuery()->where('school_id', $schoolId)->whereKey($id)->first();
```

## A03 Injection

**Backend — always Form Request validation; never trust `$request->all()` for mass assign.**

```php
// ❌ BAD
User::create($request->all());
DB::select("SELECT * FROM news WHERE title = '$search'");

// ✅ GOOD — Eloquent bindings + validated input
News::create($request->validated());
$query->where('title', 'like', $search.'%'); // avoid leading %
```

- Use Eloquent / query builder only — no raw SQL with string concat.
- `$fillable` or `$guarded` on every model; never pass unvalidated keys to `create()`/`update()`.
- Validate file uploads: `mimes`, `max`, store outside `public/` with signed URLs or controlled route.

**Frontend — Zod `safeParse()` before submit; never `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without DOMPurify.**

## A07 Authentication

- Login: throttle `Route::middleware('throttle:5,1')` on `admin/login`.
- Passwords: bcrypt via Laravel `Hash::make()` — never log or return passwords.
- Sanctum tokens: revoke on logout; short-lived tokens for SPA if possible.
- Generic error on failed login: `"Kredensial tidak valid."` — do not reveal if email exists.

## A05 Misconfiguration

- `APP_DEBUG=false` in production; never expose stack traces to clients.
- Secrets in `.env` only — never commit `.env`, API keys, or tokens.
- `CACHE_STORE=file` — no Redis; still sanitize all inputs.
- CORS: restrict `SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS` to known frontend origins.

## A09 Logging

Log security events (failed login, 403 admin access, validation abuse) — never log passwords or tokens.

## Pre-merge checklist

- [ ] Form Request / Zod on every input endpoint
- [ ] Admin mutations behind Sanctum + admin middleware
- [ ] No raw SQL; search uses bound parameters
- [ ] Mass assignment guarded
- [ ] Rate limit on auth and public POST (`pmb/registrations`)
- [ ] API Resources hide internal fields (`password`, tokens)
